Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Located just east of downtown Tampa and north of Apollo Beach, the East Tampa submarket provides direct access to major interstate corridors including east/west access via Interstate 4 and north/south access via Interstate 75. This access to both customers and talent make East Tampa a desirable location to conduct business across the state and beyond. Strong occupier demand from household names has driven submarket vacancy to just 3.0%, with much of relatively limited upcoming construction already spoken for. East Tampa’s infill location is home to a wide variety of corporations including HD Supply, RJ Schinner, Coca Cola, Dealer Tire, JB Hunt, Wayfair, Pride Mobility, Snyders Lance, Sleep Number, Lowes Maintenance Supply, and Bridgestone just to name a few.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located in the very tight East Tampa Industrial sub-market, this project has 390,711 square feet of available space, which is difficult to find anywhere else in East Tampa and is one of the largest existing blocks of space in the Tampa MSA. This industrial facility offers an abundance of loading with 32 docks, ample electric and visibility on US Highway 301. This property’s open floor plan and limited office build-out can easily meet the needs of a wide variety of users.
